{{Infobox person | name = Antônio Luiz Seabra | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = Antônio Luiz Da Cunha Seabra | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | restingplace = | nationality = Brazilian | residence = London, England | education = | alma mater = | occupation = | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | known for = founder and largest shareholder, [[Natura]] | boards = | salary = | networth = US$ 1.37 billion (June 2017)<ref name="forbes1">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/antonio-luiz-seabra/ |title=Antonio Luiz Seabra |publisher=Forbes.com |accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref> | spouse = married | children = 4 | parents = | relations = | website = }} '''Antônio Luiz Da Cunha Seabra''' is a Brazilian billionaire businessman, and the founder and largest shareholder of the Brazilian cosmetics company [[Natura]].
Seabra has a bachelor's degree in economics.<ref name="forbes1"/>
Seabra founded Natura in 1969, and it started using a similar business model to Avon, selling door-to-door.<ref name="forbes1"/>
He owns [[Bresco]], a Brazilian "property-rental operation focused on industrial property, warehouses, offices and hotels".<ref name="forbes1"/>
Seabra is married, with four children, and lives in London, England.<ref name="forbes1"/> He has been based in London since at least 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author=Heather Stewart |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2007/mar/11/theobserver.observerbusiness5 |title=Super-rich home in on London &#124; Business |publisher=The Guardian |date=2007-03-11 |accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref>
