'''Carrie Lee Sze Kei''' ({{zh|t=李詩琪|s=李诗琪|p=Lí Sīqī}}; born 12 December 1985) is a [[Malaysian Chinese]] actress, model, and businesswoman. 准拿督李诗琪 won for the country, Malaysia in Hong Kong defeated 9335 contestants from all over the world.

==Early life and career==
Lee was born in [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]. She is a third generation [[Malaysian Chinese]]. Describing her own personality, she stated that she rarely cried as a child.<ref name="Sina20041108">{{citation|url=http://eladies.sina.com.cn/2004-11-08/121393.html|periodical=Sina News|date=8 November 2004|title=冠军女孩李诗琪的美丽心情|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> She did her education at [[SMK Segambut Jaya]] ([[:ms:Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Segambut Jaya|see Malaysian Wikipedia]]) in [[Segambut]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], and represented the [[Federal Territory (Malaysia)|Federal Territory]] in [[Team handball|handball]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://thestar.com.my/lifestyle/story.asp?file=/2005/1/31/features/10002495&sec=features |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019145451/http://thestar.com.my/lifestyle/story.asp?file=%2F2005%2F1%2F31%2Ffeatures%2F10002495&sec=features |dead-url=yes |archive-date=19 October 2012 |periodical=The Star |date=31 January 2005 |accessdate=26 September 2011 |title=Carrie Lee is out of this world |last=Tham |first=Ai-Mei |df=dmy-all }}</ref> During her school days, she was known as a tomboy, an image which she later chose to shed.<ref>{{citation |url=http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2004/10/17/nation/9156861&sec=nation |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20050404202156/http://thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=%2F2004%2F10%2F17%2Fnation%2F9156861&sec=nation |dead-url=yes |archive-date=4 April 2005 |periodical=The Star |date=17 October 2004 |accessdate=27 September 2011 |title=Former 'Tomboy' to represent Malaysia at pageant in Hong Kong |last=Ng |first=Cheng-Yee |df=dmy-all }}</ref>

She represented Malaysia in [[Miss Tourism International]] 2003 and placed Top 15. In 2004, Lee represented Malaysia in the Miss Chinese Cosmos beauty pageant. During the proceedings, she spoke Chinese rather stammeringly, which observers suggested could be a barrier to her carrying out her duties as title-holder; nevertheless, she went on to win the top prize.<ref name="Sina20041108"/> In media interviews following her victory, she stated that she hoped to become an actress.<ref>{{citation|url=http://ent.enorth.com.cn/system/2004/12/04/000917682.shtml|date=4 December 2004|accessdate=27 September 2011|title=中华小姐冠军亮相 李诗琪我适合演戏|periodical=Tianjin North News}}</ref> The following year, she entered [[Jinan University]]'s Chinese Department as a short-term student to study [[Chinese language|Chinese]]. Her oral skills showed significant improvement compared to the Miss Chinese Cosmos proceedings, but she was still not able to read or [[written Chinese|write Chinese]] aside from her own name. She hoped that studying at Jinan University would help her to become literate in Chinese and appreciate [[Chinese culture]].<ref>{{citation|url=http://edu.sina.com.cn/y/i/2005-09-01/102542731.html|date=1 September 2005|periodical=Sina News|title=中华小姐李诗琪求学暨大 第一天上课学写拍马屁|accessdate=27 September 2011}}</ref> She returned to Malaysia in 2005.<ref name="AsiaOne20110712">{{citation |url=http://business.asiaone.com/Business/My%2BMoney/Property/Story/A1Story20110712-288766.html |date=12 July 2011 |accessdate=26 September 2011 |title=Carried away by Miss Lee |last=Wilson |first=Willy |periodical=The Star |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902052019/http://business.asiaone.com/Business/My%2BMoney/Property/Story/A1Story20110712-288766.html |archivedate=2 September 2011 |df=dmy }}</ref> By 2007, she had appeared in two Chinese-language television series in Malaysia, and worked as a promotional model for [[Pepsi]], [[Matsushita]], and [[Sony]].<ref name="Phoenix">{{citation|url=http://phtv.ifeng.com/program/lyyy/xxz/200709/0910_1619_242294_1.shtml|date=10 September 2007|accessdate=26 September 2011|title=最无悬念的选美理由：李诗琪，目标星光大道|periodical=[[Phoenix Television]]}}</ref> She later went into business, purchasing the Miss Chinese Cosmos franchise for Malaysia, and founding White Fairy Sdn. Bhd., an [[event planning]] company.<ref name="AsiaOne20110712"/> She also host tourism programme (States in Malaysia) 13 episodes Wayang
Tinggi Production House for RTM.

