'''Pioneer Park Cemetery''' is a conglomeration of four graveyards with the remains of several of the city’s earliest founders. It is located in the [[Convention Center District, Dallas, Texas|Convention Center District]] of [[downtown Dallas|downtown]] [[Dallas, Texas|Dallas]], [[Texas]] ([[United States|USA]]) and directly east of [[Pioneer Plaza]]. It is the final resting place for four Dallas mayors, the city's early business leaders and heroes of the Texas revolution. Also located in the cemetery is the [[Confederate War Memorial (Dallas, Texas)|Confederate War Memorial]].

